# Nyaya — Infrastructure

Firebase + Python bridge for the [Nyaya](https://yatj-nyaya-api.hf.space) AI fairness audit platform.  
Google Solution Challenge 2026.

---

## What This Repo Does

This is the infrastructure layer that connects Nyaya's HuggingFace backend to Firebase Firestore, so the Flutter app can stream live audit results.

**Flow:**
---

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `write_test_doc.py` | Run once to seed a test Firestore document (`audit_jobs/test-001`) with realistic fake data. Lets Member B test their Results screen before full integration. |
| `write_to_firestore.py` | Main bridge script. Calls `/audit` then `/retroactive` on the HF API, writes all results to Firestore. Use as fallback if Flutter's direct API call has issues. |
| `data/demo_dataset.csv` | 200-row synthetic Indian hiring dataset with caste/religion labels. Used for all integration tests. |
| `serviceAccountKey.json` | **NOT committed.** Get from Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts → Generate New Private Key. |

---

## Setup

```bash
pip install firebase-admin requests
```

Place `serviceAccountKey.json` in the repo root (do not commit it — it's in `.gitignore`).

---

## Usage

**Seed a test document (run once, for Member B's testing):**
```bash
python write_test_doc.py
# → writes audit_jobs/test-001 to Firestore
# → tell Member B to use jobId "test-001"
```

**Run a real audit job:**
```bash
python write_to_firestore.py data/demo_dataset.csv my-job-id-001
# → calls HF API /audit + /retroactive
# → writes results to Firestore audit_jobs/my-job-id-001
# → tell Member B to use this jobId
```

Takes 5–10 minutes. Watch terminal output for progress.

---

## Firestore Schema

**`audit_jobs/{jobId}`**

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `status` | string | `running` → `audit_complete` → `complete` (or `error`) |
| `model_name` | string | Name of the model being audited |
| `caste_seat_before` / `caste_seat_after` | float | SEAT d-score before/after debiasing |
| `religion_seat_before` / `religion_seat_after` | float | Religion bias d-score |
| `demographic_parity_before` / `demographic_parity_after` | float | Shortlist rate ratio across groups |
| `passes_fairness` | bool | True if model passes 80/20 fairness rule after debiasing |
| `shortlist_rates_before` / `shortlist_rates_after` | map | Per-group shortlist % e.g. `{brahmin: 72.0, dalit: 29.0}` |
| `gemini_explanation` | string | Gemini-generated plain-English explanation of results |
| `dataset_rows` | int | Number of rows in uploaded CSV |
| `created_at` / `completed_at` | timestamp | Job lifecycle timestamps |

**`audit_jobs/{jobId}/retroactive_results/{id}`** — one document per applicant with their individual before/after outcome.

---

## Firestore Rules (Hackathon)

Open rules are set for the duration of the hackathon:

```js
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /{document=**} {
      allow read, write: if true;
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Backend API

Live at: **https://yatj-nyaya-api.hf.space**

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/health` | GET | Wake check — always call this 5 min before a demo |
| `/audit` | POST | Upload CSV, returns SEAT d-scores + Gemini explanation |
| `/retroactive` | POST | Upload CSV, returns per-applicant before/after decisions |

> ⚠️ HF Spaces free tier sleeps after 48 hours. Run `curl https://yatj-nyaya-api.hf.space/health` before every demo/integration test.

---

## Integration Test

```bash
python write_to_firestore.py data/demo_dataset.csv integration-test-001
```

Then open Firebase Console → Firestore → `audit_jobs/integration-test-001`.  
Status should reach `complete` with all metric fields populated within 8 minutes.  
Share the jobId with Member B to verify their Results screen.

